  <h2 class="no-margin subsection-header" data-anchor="ember-tooltips">
    Ember Tooltips
    <small class="header-link"><LinkTo @route="index" @query={{hash anchor="ember-tooltips"}}><FaIcon @icon="link" /></LinkTo></small>
  </h2>
  <h4 class="dark-gray text-weight-normal">(dependency)</h4>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-5">
      <p>Labs UI depends the <a href="https://github.com/sir-dunxalot/ember-tooltips/">Ember Tooltips</a> addon for its tooltips. This addon also has Popovers. What's the difference? Tooltips are for read-only purposes, whereas Popovers can contain interactive elements. See <a href="http://sir-dunxalot.github.io/ember-tooltips/">the docs</a> for how to use Ember Tooltips.</p>
      <p>Labs UI also has a custom Sass module which helps Ember Tooltips more closely match our styles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-7">
      <p>By default, Tooltips have a dark background and Popovers have a light background:</p>
      <button class="button">
        Hover me for a Tooltip
        <EmberTooltip @text="This is just a regular tooltip." />
      </button>
      <span class="button">
        Click me for a Popover
        <EmberPopover @event="click">
          <h4 class="small-margin-bottom">This is a popover!</h4>
          <p>You can <a href="#">interact</a> with elements in a popover.</p>
          <input type="text">
        </EmberPopover>
      </span>
      <p>The Popover can be given a dark background with the <code>.dark</code> class:</p>
      <pre><code>&lt;EmberPopover @_tooltipVariantClass="ember-popover dark">
...
&lt;/EmberPopover></code></pre>
      <span class="button">
        Click me for a Dark Popover
        <EmberPopover @event="click" @_tooltipVariantClass="ember-popover dark">
          <h4 class="small-margin-bottom">This is a dark popover!</h4>
          <p>You can <a href="#">interact</a> with elements in a popover.</p>
          <input type="text">
        </EmberPopover>
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>


